  "What does 'enthalpy of atomization' mean?": "",
  "The energy needed to split a nucleus": "",
  "The enthalpy change to convert one mole of a substance into gaseous atoms": "",
  "The energy released when atoms bond": "",
  "The enthalpy of a nuclear reaction": "",
  "The enthalpy of atomization is the energy required to break all bonds in one mole of a substance and separate it into individual gaseous atoms.": "",
